p.s: For each variable, weighted proportions and unweighted n refer to survey participants who provided the information.
Unweighted n may vary due to missing values.

Odds ratio (OR) and 95% confidence interval (95%CI) obtained from multivariable logistic regression analyses; crude OR 0 ; 1 OR adjusted for age groups and gender; 2 OR adjusted for age groups and gender plus body mass index status, educational attainment status, and smoking status.
3 OR additionally adjusted for comorbidities, 4 OR additionally adjusted for urban-rural residence and having a personal family physician.

For all measure but inhalation technique monitoring and smoking cessation advice for current smokers, rates refer to population with current asthma; * process measure on inhalation technique monitoring refers to population with current asthma and prescription inhaler; and ** process measure on smoking cessation advice refers to population with current asthma and self-reported current smoking.
